school_type <- table(alumni$private)

labels <- c("Public", "Private")
percentages <- round(100 * school_type / sum(school_type), 1)
pie_labels <- paste(labels, percentages, "%")

pie(school_type, 
    labels = pie_labels, 
    main = "Proportion of Private vs Public Schools", 
    col = c("red", "green"))

#take out school
alumni$school <- NULL
pairs(alumni)

#Split data set into training and testing data
train.split <- sample.int(nrow(alumni), 0.75*nrow(alumni))
train <- alumni[train.split,]
test <- alumni[-train.split,]
n <- nrow(train)
#set base model and full model for forward filling
base <- lm(log(alumni_giving_rate) ~ 1, data = train)
full <- lm(log(alumni_giving_rate) ~ . + .^2, data = train)
#do forward fill
fwdBIC <- step(base, scope=formula(full), direction="forward", k=log(n))

We now have a line that depends on whether the institution is private or not. The intercept will change based on this

Intercept: private = 1 -> 3.53056 + 1*0.43955 = 3.97011

model @ private = 1: giving rate = 3.97011 - 0.04705 * student_faculty_ratio

model @ private = 0: giving rate = 3.53056 - 0.04705 * student_faculty_ratio

plot(fwdBIC, which=1)
